value: Full leather with extensive gilding on front cover. "Bound by Zaehnsdorf" (undated)

First work for A ATBB soli, SSATB chorus, fl1, fl2, ob1, ob2, tpt1, vl1, vl2, vl1, bc ; 2nd work for SB soli, vl1, vl2, vla, bc. ; 3rd work for vl, b.
First line first work: Of old when heroes
Second work first performed in 1690. The movements are in the order Z. 572 no. 3, First musick ; 5, Second musick ; 6, 3rd musick [title crossed out] ; 1. Ouverture ;  2, 1st Act tune ; 8, 2d Act tune ; 9, Caelia that I once was blest ; 7, [4th] Act tune ; 10, [For] Iris I sigh and hourly dye ; Z. D253, Dance for tinkers ; 11, Fair Iris and her swain.
Third work is placed among the movements of the second work.
Cover title.
Singers named in the second work: Mrs. Butler (S), Mr. Bowman (B)
Thematic catalogue nos. Z. 333, Z. 572 and D253.
Copyist's manuscript in ink.
Paper: 12 staves (275x164mm); watermark: Arms of Amsterdam.
Original pagination 115-172 (continued in GB Ob MS.Tenbury.785).
Former shelf mark: 31.H.13 (also numbered C. 659-660, and listed as such in the Zimmerman thematic catalogue)
